/html/body/div/text()[1]
GREATER CHONGQING, THE UNITED FEDERATION OF CHINA

====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[1]:0,92
[At its prewar height, this region boasted a population of over thirty-five million people.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[1]:92,130
Now, there are barely fifty thousand.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[1]:130,281
Reconstruction funds have been slow to arrive in this part of the country, the government choosing to concentrate on the more densely populated coast.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[1]:281,357
There is no central power grid, no running water besides the Yangtze River.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[1]:357,467
But the streets are clear of rubble and the local “security council” has prevented any postwar outbreaks.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[1]:467,638
The chairman of that council is Kwang Jingshu, a medical doctor who, despite his advanced age and wartime injuries, still manages to make house calls to all his patients.]
====
