====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:0,67
Before the outbreak started, overland smuggling was never popular.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:67,189
To arrange for the passports, the fake tour buses, the contacts and protection on the other side all took a lot of money.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:189,261
Back then, the only two lucrative routes were into Thailand or Myanmar.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:261,343
Where I used to live, in Kashi, the only option was into the ex-Soviet republics.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:343,417
No one wanted to go there, and that is why I wasn’t initially a shetou.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:417,544
1 I was an importer: raw opium, uncut diamonds, girls, boys, whatever was valuable from those primitive excuses for countries.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:544,575
The outbreak changed all that.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:575,706
Suddenly we were besieged with offers, and not just from the liudong renkou, 2 but also, as you say, from people on the up-and-up.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:706,787
I had urban professionals, private farmers, even low-level government officials.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:787,828
These were people who had a lot to lose.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[37]:828,898
They didn’t care where they were going, they just needed to get out.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[38]
Did you know what they were fleeing?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[39]:0,25
We’d heard the rumors.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[39]:25,73
We’d even had an outbreak somewhere in Kashi.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[39]:73,121
The government had hushed it up pretty quickly.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[39]:121,165
But we guessed, we knew something was wrong.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[40]
Didn’t the government try to shut you down?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[41]:0,21
Officially they did.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[41]:21,97
