====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[182]:962,1081
From 1973 onward, if nine intelligence analysts came to the same conclusion, it was the duty of the tenth to disagree.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[182]:1081,1171
No matter how unlikely or far-fetched a possibility might be, one must always dig deeper.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[182]:1171,1547
If a neighbor’s nuclear power plant might be used to make weapons-grade plutonium, you dig; if a dictator was rumored to be building a cannon so big it could fire anthrax shells across whole countries, you dig; and if there was even the slightest chance that dead bodies were being reanimated as ravenous killing machines, you dig and dig until you stike the absolute truth.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:0,31
And that is what I did, I dug.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:31,58
At first it wasn’t easy.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:58,200
With China out of the picture…the Taiwan crisis put an end to any intelligence gathering…I was left with very few sources of information.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:200,337
A lot of it was chaff, especially on the Internet; zombies from space and Area 51…what is your country’s fetish for Area 51, anyway?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:337,482
After a while I started to uncover more useful data: cases of “rabies” similar to Cape Town…it wasn’t called African rabies until later.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:482,592
I uncovered the psychological evaluations of some Canadian mountain troops recently returned from Kyrgyzstan.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[183]:592,699
I found the blog records of a Brazilian nurse who told her friends all about the murder of a heart surgeon.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[184]:0,72
The majority of my information came from the World Health Organization.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[184]:72,182
The UN is a bureaucratic masterpiece, so many nuggets of valuable data buried in mountains of unread reports.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[184]:182,277
I found incidents all over the world, all of them dismissed with “plausible” explanations.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[184]:277,356
These cases allowed me to piece together a cohesive mosaic of this new threat.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[184]:356,454
The subjects in question were indeed dead, they were hostile, and they were undeniably spreading.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[184]:454,531
I also made one very encouraging discovery: how to terminate their existence.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[185]
Going for the brain.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[186]:0,197
[He chuckles.] We talk about it today as if it is some feat of magic, like holy water or a silver bullet, but why wouldn’t destruction of the brain be the only way to annihilate these creatures?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[186]:197,246
Isn’t it the only way to annihilate us as well?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[187]
You mean human beings?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[188]:0,36
[He nods.] Isn’t that all we are?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[188]:36,114
Just a brain kept alive by a complex and vulnerable machine we call the body?
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[188]:114,240
The brain cannot survive if just one part of the machine is destroyed or even deprived of such necessities as food or oxygen.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[188]:240,416
That is the only measurable difference between us and “The Undead.” Their brains do not require a support system to survive, so it is necessary to attack the organ itself.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[188]:416,542
[His right hand, in the shape of a gun, rises to touch his temple.] A simple solution, but only if we recognized the problem!
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[188]:542,671
Given how quickly the plague was spreading, I thought it might be prudent to seek confirmation from foreign intelligence circles.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:0,90
Paul Knight had been a friend of mine for a long time, going all the way back to Entebbe.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:90,157
The idea to use a double of Amin’s black Mercedes, that was him.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:157,310
Paul had retired from government service right before his agency’s “reforms” and gone to work for a private consulting firm in Bethesda, Maryland.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:310,509
When I visited him at his home, I was shocked to find that not only had he been working on the very same project, on his own time, of course, but that his file was almost as thick and heavy as mine.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:509,568
We sat up the whole night reading each other’s findings.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:568,589
Neither of us spoke.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:589,707
I don’t think we were even conscious of each other, the world around us, anything except the words before our eyes.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[189]:707,789
We finished almost at the same time, just as the sky began to lighten in the east.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[190]
Paul turned the last page, then looked to me and said very matter-of-factly, “This is pretty bad, huh?” I nodded, so did he, then followed up with “So what are we going to do about it?”
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[191]
And that is how the “Warmbrunn-Knight” report was written.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[192]:0,42
I wish people would stop calling it that.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[192]:42,268
There were fifteen other names on that report: virologists, intelligence operatives, military analysts, journalists, even one UN observer who’d been monitoring the elections in Jakarta when the first outbreak hit Indonesia.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[192]:268,398
Everyone was an expert in his or her field, everyone had come to their own similar conclusions before ever being contacted by us.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[192]:398,446
Our report was just under a hundred pages long.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[192]:446,592
It was concise, it was fully comprehensive, it was everything we thought we needed to make sure this outbreak never reached epidemic proportions.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[192]:592,820
I know a lot of credit has been heaped upon the South African war plan, and deservedly so, but if more people had read our report and worked to make its recommendations a reality, then that plan would have never needed to exist.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[193]:0,49
But some people did read and follow your report.
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[193]:49,71
Your own government…
====
/html/body/div/div[1]/p[194]
