/html/body/div/div[5]/p[3]:0,84
It stretched to the horizon: sedans, trucks, buses, RVs, anything that could drive.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[3]:84,122
I saw tractors, I saw a cement mixer.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[3]:122,277
Seriously, I even saw a flatbed with nothing but a giant sign on it, a billboard advertising a “Gentlemen’s Club.” People were sitting on top of it.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[3]:277,354
People were riding on top of everything, on roofs, in between luggage racks.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[3]:354,449
It reminded me of some old picture of trains in India with people hanging on them like monkeys.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[4]:0,89
All kinds of crap lined the road—suitcases, boxes, even pieces of expensive furniture.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[4]:89,185
I saw a grand piano, I’m not kidding, just smashed like it was thrown off the top of a truck.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[4]:185,226
There were also a lot of abandoned cars.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[4]:226,297
Some had been pushed over, some were stripped, some looked burned out.
====
