====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[4]:609,650
It wouldn’t make sense, but…[shrugs].
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:0,76
Back down the road, about thirty miles, traffic was moving a little better.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:76,116
You’d think the mood would be calmer.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:116,129
It wasn’t.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:129,230
People were flashing their lights, bumping the cars in front of them, getting out and throwing down.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:230,309
I saw a few people lying by the side of the road, barely moving or not at all.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:309,434
People were running past them, carrying stuff, carrying children, or just running, all in the same direction of the traffic.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[5]:434,463
A few miles later, I saw why.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:0,46
Those creatures were swarming among the cars.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:46,148
Drivers on the outer lanes tried to veer off the road, sticking in the mud, trapping the inner lanes.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:148,184
People couldn’t open their doors.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:184,218
The cars were too tightly packed.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:218,305
I saw those things reach in open windows, pulling people out or pulling themselves in.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:305,343
A lot of drivers were trapped inside.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:343,394
Their doors were shut and, I’m assuming, locked.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:394,454
Their windows were rolled up, it was safety tempered glass.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:454,517
The dead couldn’t get in, but the living couldn’t get out.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:517,624
I saw a few people panic, try to shoot through their windshields, destroying the only protection they had.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:624,632
Stupid.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:632,719
They might have bought themselves a few hours in there, maybe even a chance to escape.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:719,766
Maybe there was no escape, just a quicker end.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:766,833
There was a horse trailer, hitched to a pickup in the center lane.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:833,872
It was rocking crazily back and forth.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[6]:872,901
The horses were still inside.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[7]:0,132
The swarm continued among the cars, literally eating its way up the stalled lines, all those poor bastards just trying to get away.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[7]:132,207
And that’s what haunts me most about it, they weren’t headed anywhere.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[7]:207,279
This was the I-80, a strip of highway between Lincoln and North Platte.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[7]:279,360
Both places were heavily infested, as well as all those little towns in between.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[7]:360,397
What did they think they were doing?
====
