====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:0,12
Brilliance.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:12,38
Sheer fucking brilliance.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:38,237
Conventional executions might have reinforced discipline, might have restored order from the top down, but by making us all accomplices, they held us together not just by fear, but by guilt as well.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:237,321
We could have said no, could have refused and been shot ourselves, but we didn’t.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:321,350
We went right along with it.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:350,494
We all made a conscious choice and because that choice carried such a high price, I don’t think anyone ever wanted to make another one again.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:494,574
We relinquished our freedom that day, and we were more than happy to see it go.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:574,691
From that moment on we lived in true freedom, the freedom to point to someone else and say “They told me to do it!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[87]:691,791
It’s their fault, not mine.” The freedom, God help us, to say “I was only following orders.”
