A mercenary sounds like some crazed-out ’Nam vet, all tats and handlestache, humpin’ in some Third World cesspool ’cause he can’t hack it back in the real world.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[91]:526,551
That wasn’t me at all.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[91]:551,843
Yeah, I was a vet, and yeah, I used my training for cash…funny thing about the army, they always promise to teach you “marketable skills,” but they never mention that, by far, there’s nothing more marketable than knowing how to kill some people while keeping others from being killed.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[92]:0,66
Maybe I was a mercenary, but you’d never know it to look at me.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[92]:66,149
I was clean-cut, nice car, nice house, even a housekeeper who came in once a week.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[92]:149,262
I had plenty of friends, marriage prospects, and my handicap at the country club was almost as good as the pros.
====
