Some of the others though…real pricks all high on the smell of their own piss.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[98]:558,613
Just rude and pushy and ordering everyone else around.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[98]:613,787
One guy sticks out in my mind, only because he wore this baseball cap that read “Get It Done!” I think he was the chief handler of the fat fuck who won that talent show.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[98]:787,838
That guy must have had fourteen people around him!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[98]:838,1019
I remember thinking at first that it would be impossible to take care of all these people, but after my initial tour of the premises, I realized our boss had planned for everything.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:0,62
He’d transformed his home into a survivalists’ wet dream.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:62,215
He had enough dehydrated food to keep an army fed for years, as well as an endless supply of water from a desalinizer that ran right out into the ocean.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:215,329
He had wind turbines, solar panels, and backup generators with giant fuel tanks buried right under the courtyard.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:329,455
He had enough security measures to hold off the living dead forever: high walls, motion sensors, and weapons, oh the weapons.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:455,648
Yeah, our boss had really done his homework, but what he was most proud of was the fact that every room in the house was wired for a simultaneous webcast that went out all over the world 24/7.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:648,735
This was the real reason for having all his “closest” and “best” friends over.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:735,845
He didn’t just want to ride out the storm in comfort and luxury, he wanted everyone to know he’d done it.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[99]:845,917
That was the celebrity angle, his way of ensuring high-profile exposure.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[100]:0,129
Not only did you have a webcam in almost every room, but there was all the usual press you’d find on the Oscar’s red carpet.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[100]:129,201
I honestly never knew how big an industry entertainment journalism was.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[100]:201,277
There had to be dozens of them there from all these magazines and TV shows.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[100]:277,324
“How are you feeling?” I heard that a lot.
====
