====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:0,167
For me, the most surreal moment was standing in the kitchen with some of the staff and other bodyguards, all of us watching the news that was showing, guess what, us!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:167,304
The cameras were literally in the other room, pointed at some of the “stars” as they sat on the couch watching another news channel.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:304,624
The feed was live from New York’s Upper East Side; the dead were coming right up Third Avenue, people were taking them on hand to hand, hammers and pipes, the manager of a Modell’s Sporting Goods was handing out all his baseball bats and shouting “Get ’em in the head!” There was this one guy on rollerblades.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:624,706
He had a hockey stick in his hand, a big ’ole meat cleaver bolted to the blade.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:706,784
He was doing an easy thirty, at that speed he might have taken a neck or two.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:784,1021
The camera saw the whole thing, the rotted arm that shot out of the sewer drain right in front of him, the poor guy back flipping into the air, coming down hard on his face, then being dragged, screaming, by his ponytail into the drain.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[101]:1021,1124
At that moment the camera in our living room swung back to catch the reactions of the watching celebs.
