/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:0,20
India and Pakistan.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:20,80
Like North and South Korea or NATO and the old Warsaw Pact.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:80,180
If two sides were going to use nuclear weapons against each other, it had to be India and Pakistan.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:180,264
Everyone knew it, everyone expected it, and that is exactly why it didn’t happen.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:264,371
Because the danger was so omnipresent, all the machinery had been put in place over the years to avoid it.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:371,587
The hotline between the two capitals was in place, ambassadors were on a first-name basis, and generals, politicians, and everyone involved in the process was trained to make sure the day they all feared never came.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[119]:587,676
No one could have imagined—I certainly didn’t—that events would unfold as they did.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[120]:0,63
The infection hadn’t hit us as hard as some other countries.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[120]:63,94
Our land was very mountainous.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[120]:94,124
Transportation was difficult.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[120]:124,360
Our population was relatively small; given the size of our country and when you consider that many of our cities could be easily isolated by a proportionately large military, it is not difficult to see how optimistic our leadership was.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[121]:0,68
The problem was refugees, millions of them from the east, millions!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[121]:68,132
Streaming across Baluchistan, throwing our plans into disarray.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[121]:132,211
So many areas were already infected, great swarms slouching toward our cities.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[121]:211,293
Our border guards were overwhelmed, entire outposts buried under waves of ghouls.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[121]:293,379
There was no way to close the border and at the same time deal with our own outbreaks.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[122]:0,61
We demanded that the Pakistanis get control of their people.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[122]:61,109
They assured us they were doing all they could.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[122]:109,133
We knew they were lying.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:0,111
The majority of refugees came from India, just passing through Pakistan in an attempt to reach someplace safe.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:111,165
Those in Islamabad were quite willing to let them go.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:165,254
Better to pass the problem along to another nation than have to deal with it themselves.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:254,373
Perhaps if we could have combined our forces, coordinated a joint operation at some appropriately defensible location.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:373,409
I know the plans were on the table.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:409,495
Pakistan’s south central mountains: the Pab, the Kirthar, the Central Brahui range.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:495,557
We could have stopped any number of refugees, or living dead.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:557,579
Our plan was refused.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:579,722
Some paranoid military attaché at their embassy told us outright that any foreign troops on their soil would be seen as a declaration of war.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:722,820
I don’t know if their president ever saw our proposal; our leaders never spoke to him directly.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:820,866
You see what I mean about India and Pakistan.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:866,903
We didn’t have their relationship.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:903,946
The diplomatic machinery was not in place.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[123]:946,1075
For all we know this little shit-eating colonel informed his government that we were attempting to annex their western provinces!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[124]:0,22
But what could we do?
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[124]:22,138
Every day hundreds of thousands of people crossed our border, and of those perhaps tens of thousands were infected!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[124]:138,170
We had to take decisive action.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[124]:170,198
We had to protect ourselves!
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[125]:0,53
There is a road that runs between our two countries.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[125]:53,167
It is small by your standards, not even paved in most places, but it was the main southern artery in Baluchistan.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[125]:167,289
To cut it at just one place, the Ketch River Bridge, would have effectively sealed off 60 percent of all refugee traffic.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[125]:289,346
I flew the mission myself, at night with a heavy escort.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[125]:346,384
You didn’t need image intensifiers.
====
