/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:521,602
And then you’ve got the Net Rigs…the Land Warrior combat integration system.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:602,741
It was this whole personal electronics suite that allowed each one of us to link up with each other and the higher-ups to link up with us.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:741,825
Through your eyepiece you could download maps, GPS data, real-time satellite recon.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:825,1054
You could find your exact position on a battlefield, your buddies’ positions, the bad guys…you could actually look through the video camera on your weapon, or anyone else’s, to see what’s over a hedge or around a corner.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:1054,1206
Land Warrior allowed every soldier to have the information of an entire command post, and let the command post control those soldiers as a single unit.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:1206,1298
“Netrocentric,” that’s what I kept hearing from the officers in front of the cameras.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:1298,1578
“Netrocentric” and “hyperwar.” Cool terms, but they didn’t mean shit when you’re trying to dig a fighting hole with MOPP gear and body armor, and Land Warrior and standard combat load, and all of it on the hottest day in what was one of the hottest summers on record.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[150]:1578,1644
I can’t believe I was still standing when Zack began to show up.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[151]:0,118
