I just kept thinking about mooseburgers and wild berries.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[305]:481,523
It was like heading to the Promised Land.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[305]:523,593
I knew once we headed far enough north, everything would be all right.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:0,27
For a little while it was.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:27,196
We had this great campsite right on the shore of a lake, not too many people around, but just enough to make us feel “safe,” you know, if any of the dead showed up.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:196,261
Everyone was real friendly, this big, collective vibe of relief.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:261,299
It was kind of like a party at first.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:299,412
There were these big cookouts every night, people all throwing in what they’d hunted or fished, mostly fished.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:412,542
Some guys would throw dynamite in the lake and there’d be this huge bang and all these fish would come floating to the surface.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:542,699
I’ll never forget those sounds, the explosions or the chainsaws as people cut down trees, or the music of car radios and instruments families had brought.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[306]:699,797
We all sang around the campfires at night, these giant bonfires of logs stacked up on one another.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[307]:0,194
That was when we still had trees, before the second and third waves starting showing up, when people were down to burning leaves and stumps, then finally whatever they could get their hands on.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[307]:194,271
The smell of plastic and rubber got really bad, in your mouth, in your hair.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[307]:271,346
By that time the fish were all gone, and anything left for people to hunt.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[307]:346,370
No one seemed to worry.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[307]:370,420
Everyone was counting on winter freezing the dead.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[308]
But once the dead were frozen, how were you going to survive the winter?
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[309]:0,15
Good question.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[309]:15,67
I don’t think most people thought that far ahead.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[309]:67,181
Maybe they figured that the “authorities” would come rescue us or that they could just pack up and head home.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[309]:181,366
I’m sure a lot of people didn’t think about anything except the day in front of them, just grateful that they were finally safe and confident that things would work themselves out.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[309]:366,430
“We’ll all be home before you know it,” people would say.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[309]:430,469
“It’ll all be over by Christmas.”
