Money was still worth something.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[314]:149,201
Everyone thought the banks would be reopening soon.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[314]:201,291
Whenever Mom and Dad would go looking for food, they’d always leave me with a neighbor.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[314]:291,401
I had this little survival radio, the kind you cranked for power, so we could listen to the news every night.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[314]:401,472
It was all stories of the pullout, army units leaving people stranded.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[314]:472,595
We’d listen with our road map of the United States, pointing to the cities and towns where the reports were coming from.
====
/html/body/div/div[5]/p[314]:595,621
I’d sit on Dad’s lap.
====
