====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:28,84
Most of us had family scattered throughout the country.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:84,208
We did our best to communicate with them, get a phone line working or send word with an army unit headed in that direction.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:208,332
The message was always the same: we’d be heading back out on patrol soon and their presence was required at the ceremony.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:332,425
Sometimes we’d try to make it more urgent, as if someone was dying and needed to see them.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:425,456
That was the best we could do.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:456,521
No one was allowed to go out and physically get them: too risky.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:521,588
We didn’t have multiple crews like you do on your missile boats.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:588,625
Every rating would be missed at sea.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:625,676
I pitied my shipmates, the agony of their waiting.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[58]:676,716
I was lucky that my wife and children…
