====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[123]:0,73
You couldn’t ask for a more ideal image of a prewar tropical paradise.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[123]:73,167
Flat, palm-covered islands or “motus” form a ring around a shallow, crystal-clear lagoon.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[123]:167,256
It used to be one of the few places on Earth where they cultured authentic black pearls.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[123]:256,402
I had bought a pair for my wife when we visited Tuamotus for our honeymoon, so my firsthand knowledge made this atoll the most likely destination.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[124]:0,63
Manihi had changed utterly since I was a newly married ensign.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[124]:63,175
The pearls were gone, the oysters were eaten, and the lagoon was crowded with hundreds of small, private boats.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[124]:175,245
The motus themselves were paved with either tents or ramshackle huts.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[124]:245,402
Dozens of improvised canoes either sailed or rowed back and forth between the outer reef and the dozen or so large ships that were anchored in deeper water.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[124]:402,586
The whole scene was typical of what, I guess, postwar historians are now calling “the Pacific Continent,” the refugee island culture that stretched from Palau to French Polynesia.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[124]:586,697
It was a new society, a new nation, refugees from all over the world uniting under the common flag of survival.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[125]
How did you integrate yourself into that society?
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:0,15
Through trade.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:15,70
Trade was the central pillar of the Pacific Continent.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:70,129
If your boat had a large distillery, you sold fresh water.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:129,178
If it had a machine shop, you became a mechanic.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:178,267
The Madrid Spirit, a liquefied natural gas carrier, sold its cargo off for cooking fuel.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:267,404
That was what gave Mister Song his idea for our “market niche.” He was Commander Song’s father, a hedge-fund broker from Shenzhen.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[126]:404,522
He came up with the idea of running floating power lines into the lagoon and leasing the electricity from our reactor.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[127]
 
