/html/body/div/div[15]/p[287]:0,171
On the range we practiced with metronomes, all the time the instructors saying “they ain’t in no hurry, why are you?” It was a way of keeping calm, pacing yourself.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[287]:171,213
We had to be as slow and robotic as them.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[287]:213,249
“Out G the G,” they used to say.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[288]
 
====
