====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[326]
 
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[327]:0,125
I just had to stand there, thumb up my ass, watching my partner’s POV as she crept through some forest, or marsh, or town.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[327]:125,165
Towns and cities, that was the hardest.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[327]:165,197
That was my team’s specialty.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[327]:197,209
Hound Town.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[327]:209,232
You ever heard of that?
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[328]
The K-9 Urban Warfare School?
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:0,44
That’s it, a real town: Mitchell, Oregon.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:44,100
Sealed off, abandoned, and still filled with active Gs.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:100,112
Hound Town.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:112,219
It actually should have been called Terrytown, because most of the breeds at Mitchell were small terriers.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:219,297
Little cairns and Norwiches and JRs, good for rubble and narrow choke points.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:297,354
Personally, the hound in Hound Town suited me just fine.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:354,378
I worked with a dachle.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:378,430
They were, by far, the ultimate urban war fighters.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:430,510
Tough, smart, and, especially the minis, completely at home in confined spaces.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:510,623
In fact, that’s what they were originally bred for; “badger dog,” that’s what dachshund means in German.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:623,714
That’s why they had that hot dog look, so they could hunt in low, narrow badger burrows.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:714,829
You see how that kind of breeding already made them suited to the ducts and crawl spaces of an urban battleground.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[329]:829,958
The ability to go through a pipe, an airshaft, in between walls, whatever, without losing their cool, was a major survival asset.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[330]
 
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[331]:0,21
