====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[548]:129,154
They were my own design.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[548]:154,316
We didn’t have the American battle uniforms, but we did have your marsh covers, the long, high waterproof boots with the bite-proof fiber sewn into the lining.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[548]:316,332
We needed those.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:0,95
The water was high that summer; the rains were coming hard and the Seine was a raging torrent.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:95,114
It was always wet.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:114,177
There was rot between your fingers, your toes, in your crotch.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:177,267
The water was up to your ankles almost all the time, sometimes up to your knees or waist.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:267,379
You would be on point, walking, or crawling—sometimes we had to crawl in the stinking fluid up to our elbows.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:379,425
And suddenly the ground would just fall away.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:425,488
You would splash, headfirst, into one of those unmapped holes.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:488,563
You only had a few seconds to right yourself before your gas mask flooded.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:563,632
You kicked and thrashed, your comrades would grab you and haul fast.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:632,672
Drowning was the least of your worries.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:672,823
Men would be splashing, struggling to stay afloat with all that heavy gear, and suddenly their eyes would bulge, and you’d hear their muffled cries.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:823,945
You might feel the moment they attacked: the snap or tear and suddenly you fall over with the poor bastard on top of you.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[549]:945,1101
If he wasn’t wearing the marsh covers…a foot is gone, the whole leg; if he had been crawling and went in face-first…sometimes that face would be gone.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[550]:0,183
Those were times when we called a full retreat to a defensive position and waited for the Cousteaus, the scuba divers trained to work and fight specifically in those flooded tunnels.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[550]:183,288
With only a searchlight and a shark suit, if they were lucky to get one, and, at most, two hours of air.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[550]:288,365
They were supposed to wear a safety line, but most of them refused to do so.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[550]:365,433
The lines tended to get tangled and slow up the diver’s progress.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[550]:433,572
Those men, and women, had a one in twenty chance of survival, the lowest ratio of any branch of any army, I don’t care what anyone says.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[550]:572,634
1 Is it any wonder they received an automatic Legion of Honor?
