====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:301,347
You couldn’t help but see California grays.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:347,442
Majestic animals, they were finally making a comeback after almost being hunted to extinction.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:442,541
They’d stopped being afraid of us and sometimes you could paddle out close enough to touch them.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:541,663
They could have killed us in a heartbeat, one smack of a twelve-foot tail fluke, one lunge of a thirtysomething-ton body.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:663,765
Early whalers used to call them devilfish because of the fierce fights they’d put up when cornered.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:765,815
They knew we didn’t mean them any harm, though.
====
/html/body/div/div[15]/p[738]:815,926
